00:40:51,910 --> 00:40:53,310
is for buying peace of mind

854
00:40:53,310 --> 00:40:55,620
for you and your daughter
when it comes time to inherit.

855
00:40:57,430 --> 00:40:58,910
Isn't that worth it, Mrs. Liao?

856
00:41:03,300 --> 00:41:07,300
(Such a Good Love!)

857
00:41:14,100 --> 00:41:16,490
(Global Young Filmmakers
Training Program)

858
00:41:16,490 --> 00:41:18,230
("Such a Good Love" Press Conference)

859
00:41:18,230 --> 00:41:21,060
Thankfully! It's finally over.

860
00:41:23,060 --> 00:41:25,230
There shouldn't be
any more accidents, right?

861
00:41:31,390 --> 00:41:32,180
Daji.

862
00:41:38,180 --> 00:41:38,980
What's wrong?

863
00:41:42,270 --> 00:41:43,750
I don't want to always be behind you.

864
00:41:46,230 --> 00:41:46,910
Come sit here.

865
00:41:47,350 --> 00:41:48,390
That's not what I'm saying.

866
00:41:49,500 --> 00:41:50,750
I want to be seen.

867
00:41:52,230 --> 00:41:54,310
I don't want to always
be in your shadow.

868
00:41:55,060 --> 00:41:55,980
What do you mean?

869
00:41:57,230 --> 00:41:59,020
This movie belongs to both of us.

870
00:41:59,870 --> 00:42:01,140
I want to be part of it too.

871
00:42:02,950 --> 00:42:04,230
Aren't you already part of it?

872
00:42:04,870 --> 00:42:06,540
Not in this way.

873
00:42:07,100 --> 00:42:08,950
We put in the same amount of work.

874
00:42:09,950 --> 00:42:10,910
But you're on stage,

875
00:42:10,910 --> 00:42:12,140
and I'm always in the dark.

876
00:42:12,750 --> 00:42:14,390
Why do they introduce me

877
00:42:14,620 --> 00:42:16,350
as "the director's girlfriend"
every time?

878
00:42:17,140 --> 00:42:18,750
Don't I have my own name?

879
00:42:19,660 --> 00:42:20,270
Daji,

880
00:42:21,950 --> 00:42:24,140
I've been caught up dealing
with Ms. Chao.

881
00:42:24,950 --> 00:42:27,540
I've neglected your feelings.

882
00:42:28,140 --> 00:42:30,390
Well. I'll tell the whole crew

883
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:31,760
- Zhou Shui.
- not to call you...

884
00:42:33,060 --> 00:42:33,980
What if I say

885
00:42:34,660 --> 00:42:36,750
I want to be the co-director?

886
00:42:37,540 --> 00:42:38,430
What do you say?

887
00:42:41,830 --> 00:42:42,390
Director?

888
00:42:43,910 --> 00:42:44,580
That sounds good.

889
00:42:46,180 --> 00:42:47,390
But you've never mentioned

890
00:42:47,390 --> 00:42:48,430
that you wanted to direct.

891
00:42:50,500 --> 00:42:51,500
Anyway, it's a good idea.

892
00:42:51,870 --> 00:42:52,660
The script

893
00:42:52,660 --> 00:42:53,980
is our work.

894
00:42:54,270 --> 00:42:55,500
If we can direct it together,

895
00:42:55,500 --> 00:42:56,790
it'll be even better.

896
00:42:58,060 --> 00:42:59,460
Okay. I'll talk to Man.

897
00:42:59,740 --> 00:43:00,710
- He just...
- No need.

898
00:43:02,910 --> 00:43:04,500
I talked to Mr. Man.

899
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:06,620
He agreed.

900
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:37,920
Please, put away your compromises

901
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:42,620
Get closer to the ideal world

902
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:47,870
Even if that day
comes a little slower and lonelier

903
00:43:49,680 --> 00:43:52,990
A person's broken copper and iron

904
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:56,950
Still has to be forged
into their own sword

905
00:43:57,370 --> 00:44:01,600
Dare to scorn, dare to be passionate,
dare to write

906
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:05,600
The plot of a hero's story

907
00:44:06,800 --> 00:44:10,930
The brave person says goodbye first

908
00:44:11,100 --> 00:44:14,730
The love that's worth it
is always sorry

909
00:44:14,830 --> 00:44:18,510
Once we were bold and fearless,
fighting against the world

910
00:44:18,760 --> 00:44:22,140
Only later realizing
how small and pitiful we were

911
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:26,150
The brave person says goodbye

912
00:44:26,320 --> 00:44:30,000
The love that's worth it
still leaves us in debt

913
00:44:30,230 --> 00:44:33,560
If we were more cautious
and didn't take risks back then

914
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:36,960
We might have our own fatigue

915
00:44:37,180 --> 00:44:39,390
Don't long for it

916
00:44:41,270 --> 00:44:44,500
Please answer me, I want to understand

917
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:49,260
Love is worth the passion,
worth the dark night

918
00:44:49,260 --> 00:44:55,460
Worth the stubbornness
to light up moments of flickering light

919
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:59,510
Even if we know the story's ending

920
00:45:00,170 --> 00:45:03,680
We still dare to pull on each other
a few more times

921
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:08,190
There is a trial
worth being stubborn, worth writing

922
00:45:08,320 --> 00:45:12,680
That's the chapter we loved

923
00:45:15,310 --> 00:45:19,460
The brave person says goodbye first

924
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:23,290
The love that's worth it
is always sorry

925
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:27,110
Once we were bold and fearless,
fighting against the world

926
00:45:27,270 --> 00:45:30,720
Only later realizing
how small and pitiful we were

927
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:34,830
If the ending could truly be seen

928
00:45:34,900 --> 00:45:38,630
Would we still dare to meet?

929
00:45:38,670 --> 00:45:42,200
As long as you say a time and place

930
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:45,260
I will still show up,
no regrets, no complaints

931
00:45:45,340 --> 00:45:47,610
I would rather

